  "text": "Image: NetEase Games via PolygonRyan Gilliam (he/him) has worked at Polygon for over eight years. He primarily spends his time writing guides for massively popular games like Diablo 4 \u0026 Destiny 2.Marvel Rivals, the third-person hero shooter set in the Marvel Universe, has a place to type in and redeem special codes to get bonus goodies. So far, all of these codes have come from the NetEase Games’ social channels for the game.In this Marvel Rivals guide, we’ll list out the currently active codes for the game, as of January 2025, and explain how to redeem them.Marvel Rivals codes for January 2025The active Marvel Rivals reward codes as of writing this are as follows:nwarh4k3xqy (Armor Model 42, Iron Man costume) — added Dec. 5, 2024, and expires March 5, 2025It’s unclear how often and for what purposes NetEase Games will use this code system for, but we’ll update this post with any additional codes that appear for Marvel Rivals.How to redeem codes in Marvel RivalsImage: NetEase Games via PolygonRedeeming codes in Marvel Rivals is very simple. Open the options menu from the main page by pressing start on your controller or escape on your keyboard before you select play, store, or any of the other tabs (you can also hit the cog button in the upper right part of the screen). Doing this will open the options menu (seen in the image above), allowing you to change your settings or exit the game. Select the “bundle code” option, and then punch in one of the codes above to instantly redeem your goodies to your account.When you redeem a reward, the game will play a preview for you (such as Iron Man sporting the fancy new costume you just got) and give you the option to automatically equip it before heading back to the game.For more Marvel Rivals guides, here’s a list of all Team-Up abilities, all maps and modes, and a look at the game’s roadmap.",
